    <abstract id="aspace_a12ae5b723c3febab15189ac5ef947a4">Women in the Fire Service (WFS) was formed by firefighters Linda Willing and Terese Floren in the early 1980s.  It functioned as a network and advocacy organization for women firefighters.

The collection consists of administrative files, correspondence, legal files, surveys, and conference materials related to Women in the Fire Service.  The records document the efforts by WFS to fight discrimination again women in the fire services by organizing and supporting women firefighters.  Particularly valuable are the files on individual women firefighters.</abstract>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_7156d157ee72244a4c50bb647bdfc507">Materials are in English.</langmaterial>
